IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: ADVANCING PHILANTHROPY TO ENABLE COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA TO FULFILL ITS MISSION AND VISION OF CARE, RESEARCH AND EDUCATION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ORGANIZATION WAS ORGANIZED AND EXISTS FOR THE PURPOSE OF SOLICITING AND MANAGING THE CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTIONS SOLEY FOR THE USE IN FUNDING THE OPERATIONS, CAPITAL EXPENDITURES AND SPECIAL PROGRAMS OF COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA, INC.
IRS990.Desc: THE FOUNDATION WAS ORGANIZED AND EXISTS FOR THE PURPOSE OF SOLICITING AND MANAGING THE CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTIONS SOLELY FOR THE USE IN FUNDING THE OPERATIONS, CAPITAL EXPENDITURES AND SPECIAL PROGRAMS OF COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA, INC.

SupportedOrganizationName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA INC

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S PATIENT CARE ENDOWMENT IS USED FOR ASSISTING WITH PATIENT CARE NEEDS OF THE COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA, A RELATED ORGANIZATION. THE ORGANIZATION'S PEDIATRIC CARE ENDOWMENT IS USED TO FUND THE PEDIATRIC PROGRAM.

COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA AND ITS AFFILIATES ARE NOT-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATIONS AND HAVE BEEN RECOGNIZED AS TAX-EXEMPT PURSUANT TO SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE HOSPICE FOLLOWS THE FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD'S AUTHORITATIVE GUIDANCE ON ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES. THE GUIDANCE CLARIFIES THE ACCOUNTING FOR THE RECOGNITION AND MEASUREMENT OF THE BENEFITS OF INDIVIDUAL TAX POSITIONS IN THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. TAX POSITIONS MUST MEET A RECOGNITION THRESHOLD OF MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT IN ORDER FOR THE BENEFIT OF THOSE TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECOGNIZED IN THE HOSPICE'S CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE HOSPICE HAS DETERMINED THAT IT DOES NOT HAVE ANY MATERIAL UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS OR OBLIGATIONS AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2018.

RecipientBusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA INC

RecipientTable.PurposeOfGrantTxt: ASSISTANCE WITH OPERATIONS, CAPITAL EXPENDITURES AND SPECIAL PROGRAMS

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA FOUNDATION IS A SUPPORTING ORGANIZATION OF THE COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA (ITS SOLE MEMBER). MONITORING OF FUNDS IS MAINTAINED THROUGH HIGH OVERLAP OF THE TWO ORGANIZATIONS' MANAGEMENT AND GOVERNING BODIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S SOLE MEMBER IS THE COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA, INC., A 501(C)(3) ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AT LARGE DIRECTORS SHALL BE ELECTED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA, INC. (THE SOLE MEMBER) AT ANY MEETING OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF THAT ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE RETURN WAS PREPARED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT WITH ASSISTANCE AND OVERSIGHT BY MANAGEMENT. UPON COMPLETION, THE RETURN WAS REVIEWED IN ITS ENTIRETY BY THE BUDGET FINANCE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD, FOLLOWED BY A PRESENTATION TO THE FULL BOARD FOR APPROVAL. FOLLOWING APPROVAL, THE RETURN WAS FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE REQUIRED ANNUALLY TO COMPLETE AND SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IDENTIFYING RELATIONSHIPS THAT MAY GIVE RISE TO CONFLICT. ANY PERSON DETERMINED TO HAVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS REQUIRED TO RECUSE THEMSELVES FROM ANY VOTE RELATED TO THE CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA REVIEWS AND MAKES DECISIONS ANNUALLY REGARDING COMPENSATION FOR EXECUTIVE STAFF. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE RETAINED AN INDEPENDENT CONSULTANT TO CONDUCT A COMPREHENSIVE REVIEW OF THE COMPETITIVENESS AND REASONABLENESS OF THE COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS PROVIDED TO THE FOLLOWING POSITIONS: CEO, CFO, SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT, COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT AND PHILANTHROPY AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR. A REVIEW OF COMPETITIVENESS AND REASONABLENESS FOR LIKE ORGANIZATIONS TO INCLUDE NOT-FOR-PROFIT POST-ACUTE CARE PROVIDERS AND HOSPITALS OF COMPARABLE SIZE, REGARDLESS OF GEOGRAPHY WAS CONDUCTED. TARGET MARKET AT MEDIAN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PHOTOCOPIES OF THE FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AT THE ORGANIZATION'S ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICE. IN ADDITION, RECENT FILINGS OF THE FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE ONLINE AT WWW.GUIDESTAR.ORG.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION WILL PROVIDE ANY GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS UPON REQUEST. THIS CAN BE DONE IN PERSON, BY PHONE, VIA OUR WEBSITE OR ON WWW.GUIDESTAR.COM. THE ORGANIZATION PUBLISHES A COMMUNITY REPORT IN THE LOCAL SUNDAY NEWSPAPER THAT PROVIDES SUMMARY INFORMATION OF THE PREVIOUS YEAR.
THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
THE ORGANIZATION IS DOING BUSINESS AS COMMUNITY HOSPICE & PALLIATIVE CARE FOUNDATION.

RelatedOrganizationName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: COMMUNITY MANAGEMENT COMPANY OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA INC

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMMUNITY MANAGEMENT COMPANY OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA, INC. WAS ESTABLISHED IN DECEMBER 2012 AND IS ORGANIZED AND OPERATED EXCLUSIVELY FOR CHARITABLE AND EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES, INCLUDING THE PROVISION OF PALLIATIVE CARE SERVICES AND OTHER HEALTH SERVICES TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH SERVICES OF THE PEOPLE IN THE COMMUNITY IT SERVES. AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2018, COMMUNITY MANAGEMENT COMPANY OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA, INC. HAD NOT ENGAGED IN ANY FINANCIAL TRANSACTIONS AND THEIR APPLICATION FOR EXEMPTION WAS STILL IN THE PROCESS.
